      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver benchmark problems for linear elastic structural analysis reproduced within 1% of analytical solutions.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical benchmark suite for static structural analysis demonstrates agreement with Timoshenko beam and Hertzian contact reference solutions to within 0.4%. Code verification requirements satisfied at the required gradation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates <2% change in primary QoIs (stiffness, yield force) between successive refinement levels; Richardson extrapolation applied.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted on the pedicle screw shank region, which governs bending stiffness. Richardson extrapolation yields a discretization uncertainty of 0.8% for stiffness and 1.1% for yield force. Both below the 2% criterion. Achieved level 3 confirmed."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals converge below 1e-6; contact stabilization energy below 1% of total strain energy.",
      "rationale": "Sparse direct solver employed for linear elastic runs; iterative solver residuals not applicable. For nonlinear contact iterations, force residual norm converges to 1e-7. Contact stabilization energy monitored and confirmed below 0.3% of total strain energy across all load steps."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments by a reviewer not involved in original model construction.",
      "rationale": "An independent FDA engineer reviewed boundary condition application, material property assignments, and loading protocol against the ASTM F1717 standard. No discrepancies identified. Model setup checklist completed and archived."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification that linear elastic isotropic material model with frictional contact is appropriate for titanium alloy pedicle screw under quasi-static bending below yield; sensitivity analysis on friction coefficient.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V exhibits linear elastic behavior up to approximately 880 MPa; peak stresses in the screw shank under ASTM F1717 loading remain below 650 MPa in the pre-yield regime. Isotropic linear elasticity is appropriate. Friction coefficient sensitivity analysis (μ = 0.1–0.3) shows <3% variation in stiffness QoI. Model form uncertainty is bounded and acceptable."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from certified material test reports for production-lot Ti-6Al-4V; geometry from calibrated CMM measurements of production implants; foam block modulus from supplier certification.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa) and Poisson's ratio (0.34) sourced from DePuy Synthes production-lot material test reports conforming to ASTM F136. Screw geometry derived from CMM measurements with ±5 µm accuracy. Polyurethane foam modulus from supplier certification (Grade 20 PCF, 137 MPa compressive modulus). Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (1000 samples); stiffness QoI 95th percentile uncertainty ±3.1%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 experimental constructs from production lots; dimensional inspection of tested implants; traceability of foam block lot.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs tested across two independent laboratories. All implants from the same production lot (Lot 2021-NC-75); dimensional inspection confirmed compliance with drawing tolerances. Foam block lot traceability documented. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison at the required gradation."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing at multiple clinically relevant loading rates and foam densities; environmental conditioning documented.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single displacement rate (1 mm/min) and single foam density (20 PCF). While this matches the ASTM F1717 protocol, it represents a single test condition and does not span the range of clinically relevant loading rates or bone analog densities. Achieved level (2) is below the required level (3); this is the one identified deficiency in the credibility assessment. Accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 is the regulatory standard and the single condition is the mandated comparison point."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented mapping between experimental measurements (geometry, material, boundary conditions) and FEA input parameters; no uncontrolled discrepancies.",
      "rationale": "A parameter equivalency table maps each experimental measurement (foam modulus, screw dimensions, fixator block geometry, grip compliance) to the corresponding FEA input. Discrepancies in grip compliance were characterized experimentally and incorporated as a spring boundary condition in the FEA. All parameters accounted for."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using both percent difference and normalized error metric E/uval < 1.96 for all primary QoIs; inter-laboratory variability characterized.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy the <10% percent difference criterion and E/uval < 1.96 at both laboratories. Inter-laboratory variability (CV < 5%) is within acceptable bounds. Quantitative comparison fully documented in the validation report."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the regulatory submission decision and to clinically relevant failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the vertebral column; yield force is the primary safety metric for fatigue life estimation; force at 40 mm is the ASTM F1717 pass/fail criterion. All three QoIs are directly relevant to the regulatory submission and to the clinical risk of construct failure leading to revision surgery."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activity geometry, loading, and material match the COU geometry, loading, and material; any differences are justified and bounded.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity uses production-lot non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws tested under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending — identical to the COU. The FEA model geometry, material, and boundary conditions are derived directly from the tested constructs. No surrogate geometry or scaled loading is employed. Validation activity is directly relevant to the COU."
    }
